5TM-5TMR_LYT,GAF_2,GAF_3,His_kinase,SpoVT_C Member of the two-component regulatory system BtsS BtsR, which is part of a nutrient-sensing regulatory network composed of BtsS BtsR, the low-affinity pyruvate signaling system YpdA YpdB and their respective target proteins, YjiY and YhjX. Responds to depletion of nutrients, specifically serine, and the concomitant presence of extracellular pyruvate. BtsS is a high-affinity receptor for extracellular pyruvate that activates BtsR by phosphorylation. Activation of the BtsS BtsR signaling cascade also suppresses YpdA YpdB-mediated yhjX induction

LytTR,Response_reg Member of the two-component regulatory system BtsS BtsR, which is part of a nutrient-sensing regulatory network composed of BtsS BtsR, the low-affinity pyruvate signaling system YpdA YpdB and their respective target proteins, YjiY and YhjX. Responds to depletion of nutrients, specifically serine, and the concomitant presence of extracellular pyruvate. BtsR regulates expression of yjiY by binding to its promoter region. Activation of the BtsS BtsR signaling cascade also suppresses YpdA YpdB-mediated yhjX induction
